title: Field hockey rankings for Oct. 15, 2015
text:
By Tom Hinkel | For lehighvalleylive.com on October 15, 2015 7:00 AM View/Post Comments 
The top four teams won out again in the last week with Emmaus and Moravian Academy the last of the unbeatens. 
Whitehall lost twice but remains at No. 5 after a 1-0 loss to a good Crestwood team and a 3-0 setback to Emmaus on the Green Hornets' senior night. Hackettstown moves up a notch to No. 8 with two more shutout wins. Liberty climbs to the ninth spot by virtue of its 2-1 win over Parkland while the Trojans fall two spots to No. 10. 
An interesting non-league matchup on Friday has No. 2 Moravian Academy traveling to Whitehall to play the Zephyrs on their turf field. 
Check out the full rankings by scrolling through the gallery atop this post.
